    {
      "type": "eq",
      "start": 28,
      "end": 48,
      "html": "<section class=\"slide eq\"><ul class=\"eq-lines\"><li id=\"imox7gol51c\" class=\" eq-item eq-title \" > Combining Like Terms </li><li id=\"imox7gol51d\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ 3x + 2x - 4 = 11 $$ </li><li id=\"imox7gol51e\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ 5x - 4 = 11 $$ </li><li id=\"imox7gol51f\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ 5x = 15 $$ </li><li id=\"imox7gol51g\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ x = 3 $$ </li><li id=\"imox7gol51h\" class=\" eq-item eq-line \" > Each operation reduces complexity. </li></ul><div class=\"eq-side-panel\"><div id=\"imox7gol51c-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" ><img src=\"force-intro.webp\" /></div><div id=\"imox7gol51c-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Like terms share the same variable. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51d-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > 3x and 2x are compatible. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51d-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > 3x+2x=5x </div><div id=\"imox7gol51d-sp-3\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Combine variable terms first. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51d-sp-4\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Constants remain separate. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51d-sp-5\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Simplification improves clarity. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51d-sp-6\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Avoid skipping visible steps. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51e-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" ><img src=\"eq.webp\" /></div><div id=\"imox7gol51e-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Now isolate the variable term. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51f-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Add 4 to both sides. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51f-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > 11+4=15 </div><div id=\"imox7gol51f-sp-3\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The negative constant disappears. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51f-sp-4\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Balance remains preserved. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51f-sp-5\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The equation becomes cleaner. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51f-sp-6\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Only multiplication remains. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51g-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" ><img src=\"box.webp\" /></div><div id=\"imox7gol51g-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Divide both sides by 5. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51h-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Equations become simpler stepwise. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51h-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Visible reasoning improves understanding. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51h-sp-3\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Students can track transformations. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51h-sp-4\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Logical pacing reduces confusion. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51h-sp-5\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The structure stays calm and readable. </div><div id=\"imox7gol51h-sp-6\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Every step has a clear purpose. </div></div></section>",
